  "texts": [
    "The way in which such judgments are made differs, but it typically involves, at least, three sources of information: about another's behavior, their perceived mind and their identity [29].",
    "Thus, character judgments hinge on what others do, what they seem to think and on 1 This does not deny that it is possible for non-humans to possess human characteristics.",
    "However, as a fallacy, anthropomorphism necessarily involves a kind of an error.",
    "Indeed, charges of anthropomorphism usually imply some kind of mistaken attribution of human traits [24].",
    "2 Whether AI could develop human qualities (e.g., awareness) is an open question."
  ]
